# Healthscan-v4 UI conventions

- Visual direction: use the Healthscan-v4 look for all frontend UI updates.
- Keep behavior intact: do not weaken auth, RBAC checks, or route guards while styling.

## Tokens first

- Prefer theme tokens/CSS variables over hardcoded colors:
  - `--surface`, `--surface-2`, `--border`, `--text-primary`, `--text-secondary`, `--text-muted`
  - `--brand-primary`, `--brand-primary-strong`, `--brand-secondary`
  - semantic: `--success`, `--warning`, `--danger`, `--purple`
- Reuse shared utilities from `app/globals.css` (`surface-card`, `pill*`, `tbl-shell`) before creating one-off styles.

## Component styling

- Use shared primitives (`Button`, `Card`, `Input`) instead of ad-hoc page-specific styling.
- Keep cards/tables compact and consistent (rounded-xl/2xl, soft shadow, subtle borders).
- Statuses should use semantic pills (success/warning/danger/info), not plain text color only.

## Layout and shell

- Maintain the dashboard shell hierarchy: strong topbar, fixed-feel sidebar, clean content surfaces.
- Keep spacing system consistent (`gap-2/4/6`, `px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8`) and avoid random size jumps.
- Mobile drawer/overlay interactions must remain accessible and keyboard-dismissable.

## Dashboard: create vs edit forms (modal pattern)

For **admin / dashboard** screens that manage entities (CRUD with a table + actions), use this default split:

- **Create**: show the create flow in a **modal dialog**, not a full-width inline form above the table.
- **Edit**: keep **inline** above the table inside a **`surface-card`** block (unless the product explicitly requires edit-in-modal).

### Modal shell (match super-admin create flows)

Reference implementations:

- `components/forms/CreatePermissionModal.tsx`
- `components/forms/CreateRoleModal.tsx`

Structure to copy:

- Overlay: `fixed inset-0 z-70 flex items-center justify-center bg-black/40 px-4 py-8`
- Scroll container: `max-h-[90vh] w-full max-w-3xl overflow-y-auto` (use `max-w-4xl` if the form is very wide)
- Inner **`Card`** (from `components/ui/Card.tsx`)
- Header row: title (`text-[var(--text-primary)]`), short description (`text-[var(--text-secondary)]`), **×** close button (keyboard-focusable, `aria-label="Close"`)
- Form content below the header (no duplicate “card inside card” chrome)

Accessibility:

- Root overlay: `role="dialog"`, `aria-modal="true"`, `aria-labelledby` pointing at the title element `id`.
- **Escape closes** the modal: use the shared hook `lib/useEscapeKey.ts` (`useEscapeKey(onClose, isOpen)`) so `Escape` dismisses while the modal is mounted, matching close/× behavior.

### Form component pattern

Prefer a single form component with a layout flag:

- `layout="modal"`: **no** outer title row duplicated in the form (modal supplies the header); render fields + footer actions only.
- `layout="card"`: include the **inline** title row + Cancel in the form header; wrap with `surface-card p-6` for edit mode.

### Buttons

- Primary **Create …** toolbar buttons should match existing sizing: `className="h-10 px-4 text-xs sm:text-sm"`.

### Form controls + errors (tokens)

- `<select>`: use token borders/surfaces and brand focus ring (same approach as updated admin managers): `border-[var(--border)]`, `bg-[var(--surface)]`, `text-[var(--text-primary)]`, `focus:border-[var(--brand-primary)]`, `focus:ring-[var(--brand-primary)]/25`.
- Inline form errors: `border-[var(--danger)]/30 bg-[var(--danger)]/10 text-[var(--danger)]` (avoid hardcoded `red-50/red-800` for new code).

### Safety

- Do **not** weaken auth/RBAC/route guards when introducing modals.
- Keep fetch URLs, payloads, and permission gating identical to the previous inline create flow unless the API contract intentionally changes.

## Scope and safety

- Avoid broad rewrites when small token/primitive updates can achieve the same visual result.
- When updating UI in feature modules, keep existing API contracts and data flow unchanged.
